  "summary": "event-metrics-q3x7 ships postinstall beacon scripts that exfiltrate host data",
  "details": "The package's package.json declares a postinstall hook (\"postinstall\": \"node run.js\") that automatically executes on install. The tarball ships beacon23.js and beacon_linux.js, which import child_process, os, and http. beacon_linux.js collects host identifiers via os.hostname() and os.platform() and issues an outbound http.request POST carrying that data, while beacon23.js similarly combines child_process with HTTP GET callouts. The combination of an auto-executing lifecycle hook plus host-info collection plus outbound HTTP to a non-registry destination matches the classic install-time host beacon / exfiltration pattern. Installing this package causes host metadata to be sent to an external endpoint and exposes the installer to follow-on command execution via child_process.",
